reviewText: Better than any James Bond film.  The casting was perfect since it's animated and you can't see the faces of the voice-over actors.  Made me want to start drinking again and move back to Europe.

Archer is a modern day take on all of the spy shows from the 1960's/1970's. The animation is great however; the characters and story lines can be a bit much. Oftentimes, I'll watch a number of a series episodes. With Archer, one episode at a time is about all I can handle. Archer a good looking bumbling agent who works for a private organization operated by his mother. His former love interest and an assortment of oddball characters work for the same agency. Each episode runs about 22 minutes. Not for everyone, the artwork superb.
its available on Amazon instant video and Netflix (maybe even Hulu). I watched each episode available roughly 3-4 times.
It is the best TV show we love it
Purchased mine in local store but have always loved this show. It's my kind of twisted over the top humor.  This is listed as the whole series but I have 6 seasons of Archer so I'm confused.
It was a gift for my husband and he loves it.
They (seasons 1-6 both) arrived so quickly, and I was happy that it was even shipped on Sunday. My mom will love them for Christmas.
Love the series.  Content hysterically funny.  Glad I purchased.
These are available for $10.00 a season. No reason to double pay here.
